  "decision": "Accepted",
  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry study conducted at three clinical sites, in which pump operating parameters and downstream hemolysis markers were recorded under standard-of-care CPB procedures. The study enrolled 112 consecutive adult CPB cases and logged impeller speed, flow rate, inlet/outlet pressures, and plasma-free haemoglobin at 30-minute intervals. The dataset spans the full operating envelope of interest and provides strong statistical coverage of the five flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. The observational cohort design afforded rich real-world variability in patient haematocrit and circuit priming volume, further strengthening generalisability. Reviewers noted the breadth of the dataset and the rigorous data-quality controls applied by the clinical sites. The evidence was judged sufficient to support the relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) acceptance criterion and to underpin the Accepted credibility decision at MRL 2.",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
