      "acceptanceCriteria": "Bland-Altman mean bias < 0.05 RH units between CFD predictions and empirical reference data.",
      "rationale": "Bland-Altman analysis of CFD-predicted RH versus registry-measured plasma-free haemoglobin (converted to RH units) yielded mean bias 0.031 with 95% LoA −0.12 to +0.18. The mean bias criterion is satisfied. The wide limits of agreement are attributed to inter-patient haematocrit variability inherent in the observational cohort design, which is considered acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
